ðŸ§  1. What is MySQL?

MySQL is an RDBMS â€” Relational Database Management System.
It stores data in tables (rows and columns) and allows you to create, read, update, and delete (CRUD) data using SQL (Structured Query Language).

MySQL = Database + SQL language

Itâ€™s open-source, fast, and widely used (e.g., in websites, apps, banking, etc.)



---

ðŸ§© 2. Core Database Concepts

Term	Meaning	Example

Database	A collection of related data.	StudentDB, BankDB
Table	A structure that stores data in rows and columns.	Student, Account
Row (Record)	A single entry in a table.	One studentâ€™s data
Column (Field)	A data attribute.	Name, RollNo, Age
Schema	The structure of the database (tables, columns, relationships).	â€”
Query	A command written in SQL to interact with the DB.	SELECT * FROM student;



