âš™ï¸ 3. How MySQL Works (Internally)

When you execute a query:

1. Parser â€“ checks SQL syntax.
(e.g., SELECT must come before FROM)


2. Optimizer â€“ finds the fastest way to execute the query.


3. Executor â€“ runs the plan and fetches data from storage engine (like InnoDB).


4. Storage Engine â€“ handles how data is stored and retrieved (InnoDB, MyISAM, etc.)




